nd homage.Key Features:The first book-length study of intertextuality in Virginia Woolf's novels;Offers a challenging and provocative new perspective on Woolf's art as a novelist;Develops detailed close readings offering fresh insights into individual works;Presents complex ideas in a lucid and accessible fashion."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Women Authors.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311078046840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780748626359zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780748626359423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780748626359/original  a978-3-11-078046-8  Edinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK